    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Game similar to lawn bowls, but played on ice, and consisting of two teams of four players, the lead, second, third, and skip. Each player slides a round stone, concave on the bottom and with a handle on the top, across a natural field or rink of ice toward the tee, or button, which is a fixed mark in the center of a circle, called the house, marked with concentric bands. The object of the game is for each side to get its stones closest to the center. A distinctive element of curling is the use of a brush, or broom, to clear the ice of debris in front of the sliding stone. The broom also provides balance for the curler during delivery of the stone and by the skip to direct aim.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>與草地滾球相似的遊戲，但是於冰上進行，並由兩支各包含四位球員的隊伍所組成，四位球員分別為一壘（Lead）、二壘（Second）、三壘（Third）以及隊長（Skip）。每位球員都將一個底部凹進去、頂部有手握柄的圓型石壺滑入，使其越過冰場、朝向圓心（button）。大本營（house）為位於場中央的固定標記區，圓心則是大本營區域同心圓線索標示的區塊。此遊戲的主要目的為各隊伍盡可能將其石壺投擲到最靠近圓心處。冰上石壺遊戲中一項獨特的元素為使用刷子或掃帚，將石壺前方冰面上的碎冰清除，掃帚亦可以為將石壺運入圓心區時提供平衡、直接瞄準目標。
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
